Here you will find the information about where the articles were gathered from. 
All articles were taken from the website Returning Heritgae webstie, the link to which is below.

Case Studies | UK Restitutions’, n.d. <https://www.returningheritage.com/case-studies>

All 32 articles taken were from the UK Case studies section of the website.
The files were all stored in md format because of its ease of use and balance between readability and structure

Transformations Applied:
After the original articles had been scraped an concatenated into a single md file. 
It was necessary to clean the excess text that was not part of the articles. The headers, names of other articles at the bottom of the article.
Due to the complications in which parts of the articles were necessary to removed.
It was judged that manualing removing the additional text would be faster than writing code utilising modules such as Spacy to remove the necessary complications.
